  <p class="eyebrow">Sagamok Anishnawbek · A member's living record</p>
  <h1>GR Truss: bought for $100, then funded</h1>
  <p class="lead">This is a living page. Here is what members can establish about GR Truss from the public record today. It will grow as members add what they know and see. If you can help, scroll to the bottom.</p>

  {% set banner_body %}<strong>Member-compiled and unofficial.</strong> This is a member-compiled summary, not an official communication of Sagamok Anishnawbek. Everything here is drawn from the public record or clearly marked as an open question. If you can <a href="/about#corrections">show us an inaccuracy</a>, we will correct it.{% endset %}
  {% include 'components/notice.html.twig' with { variant: 'caveat', body: banner_body, label: 'About this page' } only %}

  {% include 'components/section_heading.html.twig' with { title: 'What it is' } only %}
  <p>GR Truss (2262012 Ontario Limited) is a truss manufacturer, roof trusses, floor trusses, and wall panels, based at 177 Highway 17B in the Garden River area. It has operated under that name since 2011.</p>

  {% include 'components/section_heading.html.twig' with { title: 'How the Nation came to own it' } only %}
  <p>On April 1, 2025, Sagamok acquired 100 percent of GR Truss for a total price of <strong>one hundred dollars</strong>, through two Nation entities: 15558409 Canada Ltd and Sagamok Real Estate Holdings LP. Its board is the Chief (as President) and two councillors, one of whom is the company's Treasurer. (Source: FY2025 audited statements, Note 18; corporate registry.)</p>

  {% include 'components/section_heading.html.twig' with { title: 'What the Nation has put in since' } only %}
  <p>Since the $100 purchase, Council has approved roughly <strong>$775,000 to $900,000</strong> for GR Truss by its own motions: a $500,000 cashflow advance approved the day after the purchase, two $125,000 equity contributions, and a $150,000 advance. Much of it is operating cashflow. (See these decisions in the <a href="/communities/sagamok/conflict-register">Conflict Register</a>.)</p>

  {% include 'components/section_heading.html.twig' with { title: 'What members cannot see' } only %}
  <p>GR Truss is not named or broken out anywhere in the Nation's audited annual report. Members have no visible figure for its sales, its profit, or its losses.</p>

  {% include 'components/section_heading.html.twig' with { title: 'The expansion' } only %}
  <p>Council authorized GR Truss to pursue acquiring <strong>Timberfield Roof Truss</strong>, a 40-year manufacturer in London, Ontario, financed by borrowing (First Nations Finance Authority or BMO). Terms have not been shown to members.</p>

  {% include 'components/section_heading.html.twig' with { title: 'The assets, as far as the record shows' } only %}
  <p>A plant in the Garden River area; a site in the Carling Township Industrial Park near Parry Sound (the Nation funded lot development there); and an 8,000 square foot building acquired as part of the purchase.</p>

  {% include 'components/section_heading.html.twig' with { title: 'Open questions: what we are still finding out' } only %}
  <ul>
    <li>Is GR Truss operating today, and is the Parry Sound / Carling plant built and running?</li>
    <li>Who supplies its lumber and materials, and who are its customers? Does it buy from or sell to any Nation entity or councillor-linked business?</li>
    <li>Was the $500,000 advance repaid? It was due March 2026.</li>
    <li>What is the Timberfield acquisition price, and what is being borrowed, on what security?</li>
    <li>What did $100 actually buy? What did the audited statements value its assets at?</li>
    <li>Trade press reported a roughly $315,000 Ontario government investment in the truss maker. Who received it, and when, before or after the Nation's purchase?</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="grt-help">
    <h3>Help build the picture</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Near the Garden River plant (177 Highway 17B) or the Carling / Parry Sound site? Send a few current, dated photos from the public road: the building, the yard, lumber or finished trusses, trucks, any activity.</li>
      <li>Have you supplied, bought from, or worked at GR Truss? Tell us whether it is operating and who it deals with.</li>
      <li>Only what you can share safely: public places only, no trespassing, do not photograph or name any worker, and only your own experience. We verify before we publish.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="grt-cta">Send what you have through the <a href="/contact">contact form</a> and a member will reply.</p>
  </div>

  {% include 'components/section_heading.html.twig' with { title: 'Updates' } only %}
  <div class="grt-updates">Member contributions and new records will be added here, dated, as they come in.</div>

  <p>See also <a href="/communities/sagamok/how-its-organized">how Sagamok is organized</a>, which maps GR Truss and the Nation's other enterprises, the <a href="/communities/sagamok/conflict-register">Conflict Register</a>, and the <a href="/standard/records-request">records request</a>, which asks Council directly about the enterprises and the benefit to members.</p>

